#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi4.270"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn40.10:1.1"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā mahāmoggallāno—seyyathāpi nāma balavā puriso samiñjitaṃ vā "
"bāhaṃ pasāreyya, pasāritaṃ vā bāhaṃ samiñjeyya; evameva—jetavane antarahito "
"devesu tāvatiṃsesu pāturahosi."
msgstr ""
"And then Venerable Mahāmoggallāna, as easily as a strong person would extend "
"or contract their arm, vanished from Jeta’s Grove and reappeared among the "
"gods of the Thirty-Three."

msgctxt "sn40.10:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho sakko devānamindo pañcahi devatāsatehi saddhiṃ yenāyasmā "
"mahāmoggallāno tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā āyasmantaṃ mahāmoggallānaṃ "
"abhivādetvā ekamantaṃ aṭṭhāsi. Ekamantaṃ ṭhitaṃ kho sakkaṃ devānamindaṃ "
"āyasmā mahāmoggallāno etadavoca:"
msgstr ""
"Then Sakka, lord of gods, with five hundred deities came up to "
"Mahāmoggallāna, bowed, and stood to one side. Mahāmoggallāna said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
#. VAR: buddhasaraṇagamanaṃ → buddhaṃ saraṇagamanaṃ (bj)
msgctxt "sn40.10:2.1"
msgid "“Sādhu kho, devānaminda, buddhasaraṇagamanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "“Lord of gods, it’s good to go for refuge to the Buddha."

#. VAR: Buddhasaraṇagamanahetu → buddhaṃ saraṇagamanahetu (bj)
msgctxt "sn40.10:2.2"
msgid ""
"Buddhasaraṇagamanahetu kho, devānaminda, evam’idhekacce sattā kāyassa bhedā "
"paraṃ maraṇā sugatiṃ saggaṃ lokaṃ upapajjanti."
msgstr ""
"It’s the reason why some sentient beings, when their body breaks up, after "
"death, are reborn in a good place, a heavenly realm."

msgctxt "sn40.10:2.3"
msgid "Sādhu kho, devānaminda, dhammasaraṇagamanaṃ hoti."
msgstr "It’s good to go for refuge to the teaching."

msgctxt "sn40.10:2.4"
